  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dd4\u0daf \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dba\u0dda \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dbd\u0dcf\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0da9\u0dd2\u0db1\u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1  \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A committee to quickly bring back the Sri Lankans who went to India during the war",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A committee has been appointed by President's Secretary Mr. Saman Ekanayake to facilitate the repatriation of Sri Lankans who have gone to India as refugees due to the war.",
        "This committee has been appointed under the chairmanship of Miss Chandima Wickramasinghe, Additional Secretary to the President.",
        "The committee comprises senior officials from the Comptroller General of Immigration, Ministry of External Affairs, Registrar General's Department and Ministry of Justice.",
        "This decision was reached in the discussion held today (05) at the President's Office under the chairmanship of President's Secretary Mr. Saman Ekanayake at the request of the \"Organization for the Rehabilitation of Eelam Refugees\" (OFERR) to repatriate Sri Lankans who have gone to India as refugees due to the war.",
        "It was stated that about 58,000 Sri Lankans living in Tamil Nadu state of India are currently staying as refugees and about 3800 of them are ready to return to Sri Lanka."
      ],
